//! Stream abstractions for byte-oriented I/O.
//!
//! This module provides the fundamental behaviors and types for streaming
//! byte data through readers, writers, and transformers. Inspired by
//! Node.js streams, adapted for TML's synchronous ownership model.
//!
//! # Core Behaviors
//!
//! | Behavior | Description |
//! |----------|-------------|
//! | [`Readable`] | Byte source — anything you can `read()` from |
//! | [`Writable`] | Byte sink — anything you can `write()` to |
//!
//! # Types
//!
//! | Type | Description |
//! |------|-------------|
//! | [`ByteStream`] | In-memory read/write stream (testing, HTTP bodies) |
//! | [`BufferedReader`] | Adds line-reading and buffering to any source |
//! | [`BufferedWriter`] | Adds write buffering and auto-flush to any sink |
//!
//! # Utilities
//!
//! | Function | Description |
//! |----------|-------------|
//! | [`pipe()`] | Copy all bytes from a source to a destination |
//! | [`copy_bytes()`] | Copy up to N bytes between streams |
//! | [`read_all()`] | Read all remaining bytes into a Buffer |
//! | [`read_to_string()`] | Read all remaining bytes as a UTF-8 string |
//! | [`write_all()`] | Write all bytes, retrying on partial writes |
//!
//! # Example
//!
//! ```tml
//! use std::stream::{ByteStream, Readable, Writable, pipe}
//!
//! // Create an in-memory stream and write data
//! var src = ByteStream::from_string("Hello, streams!")
//! var dst = ByteStream::new()
//!
//! // Pipe all data from source to destination
//! let bytes = pipe(mut ref src, mut ref dst)!
//! assert_eq(dst.to_string(), "Hello, streams!")
//! ```

